main event: On July 13th, 1955 in La Habra, California, a ground-visual observation reported an oblong, dark brown object moving faster than a jet, with a 15-second observation time.
interesting points: The object was observed to be faster than a jet but insufficient data was available for evaluation.
The report suggests a possibility that the object could have been an aircraft, although it was not conclusive.
The observation lasted for 15 seconds, indicating a relatively short sighting.
The location of the sighting was noted to have clear skies with few high clouds and good visibility.
Two P-51A aircraft were orbiting Van Nuys Airport in a landing pattern at the time of the observation, but lack of details prevented further suggestions.
sighted object: oblong, dark brown object moving faster than a jet
